The Democratic Alliance’s (DA) Western Cape premier candidate, Alan Winde, will brief the media in Hout Bay on Monday morning about the party’s plan on maritime security and keeping drugs out of the province. He will be joined by the party’s spokesperson on Crime, John Steenhuisen and the Mayoral Committee Member for Safety and Security, JP Smith. They will also highlight the City of Cape Town’s coastal unit successes. Watch a related video below: 